      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed.  This is a sin of Login.vue that I should have addressed when we added vendor language override support to i18n.js.\n\nThis should be something like:\n```\nconst languages \u003d computed(() \u003d\u003e getAvailableLanguages(availableLocales));\n```\n\nand then in i18n.js:\n```\n// Build a {value, text} list for a language picker from a set of locale codes.\n// Drops bare-language aliases (those without a region suffix) so each language\n// only appears once, and resolves the native display name via Intl.DisplayNames.\nexport function getAvailableLanguages(locales) {\n  return (locales || [])\n    .filter((loc) \u003d\u003e loc.includes(\u0027-\u0027))\n    .map((loc) \u003d\u003e {\n      const language \u003d new Intl.Locale(loc).language;\n      let name;\n      try {\n        name \u003d new Intl.DisplayNames([loc], { type: \u0027language\u0027 }).of(language);\n      } catch {\n        name \u003d loc;\n      }\n      const text \u003d name\n        ? name.charAt(0).toLocaleUpperCase(loc) + name.slice(1)\n        : loc;\n      return { value: loc, text };\n    })\n    .sort((a, b) \u003d\u003e a.value.localeCompare(b.value));\n}\n```\n\nHere I used Intl.DisplayNames, otherwise every strings file would need a special key for its Display name.",
      "parentUuid": "534b53ea_4701c354",
      "revId": "4f320932e9a12767625401cb4f1a6c2fbe7c0ed4",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
